  <!-- ============================================================= -->
  <!-- GOVERNANCE                                                    -->
  <!-- ============================================================= -->
  <governance>
    <issue id="ISS-IMPL-ZERO" status="draft" owner="STK-MAINTAINER">
      <statement>
        The spec precedes the plugin: implementation coverage is zero at this
        draft, and that is the intended state. Every implements/verifiedBy
        edge will be recorded with rqml link as the corresponding artifact
        lands, and the drift baseline committed then, mirroring how
        RQML-CLAUDE-001 (ISS-IMPL-ZERO) and RQML-SELF-001 (ISS-IMPL-TRACE)
        established theirs.
      </statement>
    </issue>
    <issue id="ISS-SURFACES" status="review" owner="STK-MAINTAINER">
      <statement>
        Which Codex surfaces this plugin targets. The Codex CLI is the
        reference target; the IDE extension, desktop app, and Codex cloud
        differ in hook delivery today (plugin-local and repo-local hooks have
        documented gaps — openai/codex issues 16430, 17532, 21639). Decision
        needed on whether to document a global hooks.json fallback as a
        supported installation mode or treat non-CLI surfaces as best-effort
        until upstream stabilizes.
      </statement>
      <notes>REQ-TRUST-TRANSPARENCY makes the degraded state visible whichever way this resolves.</notes>
    </issue>
    <issue id="ISS-HOOK-EVENTS" status="review" owner="STK-MAINTAINER">
      <statement>
        Open question: whether additional Codex hook events add value beyond
        the core triad. Candidates: PostCompact re-anchoring (re-inject the
        spec summary after compaction, directly countering OBS-AGENT-DRIFT),
        UserPromptSubmit per-prompt context, and PreToolUse guarding of
        hand-edits to trace XML. Deferred until the three core hooks have
        field experience; each extra hook also grows the trust-review surface.
      </statement>
    </issue>
    <approval id="APR-MAINTAINER" role="RQML Maintainer" status="draft">
      <description>Maintainer sign-off on the rqml-codex specification.</description>
    </approval>
  </governance>

</rqml>
